<title>GERMANY: KOHL SAYS EURO TO STRENGTHEN COMPETITIVE STANCE.</title>
<headline>KOHL SAYS EURO TO STRENGTHEN COMPETITIVE STANCE.</headline>
<dateline>MUNICH, Germany 1997-03-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>German Chancellor Helmut Kohl said on Wednesday the planned single European currency, the euro, would strengthen Europe's competitive position against the dollar and yen spheres.</p>
<p>In the text of a speech prepared for delivery at a trades' conference, Kohl said speculation about which countries would participate in EMU was inappropriate at this time.</p>
<p>But recent progress in Germany and Europe on fiscal matters was grounds for optimism on EMU's chances for success, he said.</p>
</text>
